    "raw_text": "Local Government Needs in the 88th District: Borough and Township Vacancies\nMechanicsburg Borough\nCurrently, Mechanicsburg Borough does not have any open seats on boards or commissions.\nNew Cumberland Borough\nCurrently, New Cumberland Borough does not have any open seats on boards or commissions.\nShiremanstown Borough\nResidents are encouraged to check for updates if they are interested in serving on a board or commission. Open positions are currently being confirmed.\nHampden Township\nHampden Township continues to seek volunteers.\nOpenings exist on the following boards, commissions and committees:\n•\tGolf Advisory Board\n•\tCivil Service Commission\n•\tIndustrial Development Authority\n•\tPlanning Commission\n•\tZoning Hearing Board\n•\tGood Hope Ad Hoc Committee\nResidents who would like to be considered can apply through the\ntownship’s volunteer portal\n.\nHampden Township also keeps applications on file for future openings, ensuring interested residents are considered as vacancies arise.\nLower Allen Township\nOpenings exist on the following commissions and committees:\n•\tCivil Service Commission\n•\tPlanning Commission\n•\tPension Committee\nThe township welcomes new volunteers year round. Due to limited openings and long appointment terms, positions may not become available immediately, but submitting interest helps the township identify future candidates.\nResidents can apply by sending a resume and cover letter outlining qualifications to Township Manager Rebecca Davis at the Municipal Services Center, 2233 Gettysburg Road, Camp Hill, PA 17011, or by emailing rdavis@latwp.org.\nMore information about boards and commissions is available on the township website at\nlatwp.org\n.\nSign Up to Receive Legislative Email Updates\nKeep up-to-date on the latest legislative and community news. Your email address will be used strictly for legislative purposes.\nEmail*\nZIP Code\nSubscribe",
